  "response": "```json\n{\n  \"package_name\": \"gemini-cli\",\n  \"explanation\": \"The build failure was caused by a deliberate assertion `assert (builtins.trace \\\"SIMULATED FAILURE\\\" false);` on line 2 of `gemini-cli.nix`. This assertion prevents the Nix evaluator from processing the file, causing both the `nix-update` command (during evaluation) and the subsequent CI build step (`nix build .#gemini-cli`) to fail. The logs explicitly show the error message `error: assertion '((builtins).trace \\\"SIMULATED FAILURE\\\" false)' failed` at the beginning of the `gemini-cli.nix` file. This was likely added for testing the CI's error handling and needs to be removed for the nightly update to succeed.\",\n  \"fix_script\": \"#!/bin/bash\\n# Remove the deliberate assertion failure from gemini-cli.nix\\nsed -i '/assert (builtins.trace \\\"SIMULATED FAILURE\\\" false);/d' gemini-cli.nix\",\n  \"pr_description\": \"Fixed the build failure in the `gemini-cli` package by removing a simulated failure assertion. The line `assert (builtins.trace \\\"SIMULATED FAILURE\\\" false);` in `gemini-cli.nix` was causing evaluation and build failures in the CI pipeline, blocking the automated nightly updates. Removing this line restores the package to a buildable state and allows the update workflow to complete successfully.\"\n}\n```",
